abstract.p:
A novel design of thin-film crystalline silicon solar cell (TF C-Si-SC) is proposed and numerically analyzed. The reported SC has 1.0 µm thickness of C-Si with embedded dielectric silicon dioxide nanowires (NWs). The introduced NWs increase the light scattering in the active layer which improves the optical path length and hence the light absorption. The SC geometry has been optimized using particle swarm optimization (PSO) technique to improve the optical and electrical characteristics. The suggested TF C-Si-SC with two embedded NWs offers photocurrent density (Jph\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${J}_{ph}$$\end{document}) of 32.8 mA cm−2 which is higher than 18 mA cm−2 of the conventional thin film SC with an enhancement of 82.2%. Further, a power conversion efficiency of 15.9% is achieved using the reported SC.

sec.p:
Recently, the dielectric nanoparticles are used to improve the optical absorption and the generated photocurrent in TF C-Si-SCs6–10. The scattering cross sections of the dielectric nanoparticles are smaller than those of plasmonic nanoparticles. However, the dielectric nanoparticles have an incomparable low light absorption than that of plasmonic materials. Moreover, the active layer with plasmonic nanoparticles suffers from electrical degradation, owing to the plasmonic high surface recombination velocity (SRV) (106 cm s−1) at the Si/plasmonic interface7. Nunomur et al.6 have introduced tandem SC with embedded SiO2 nano-spheres with an enhancement of 16% in the short-circuit current density (Jsc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${J}_{sc}$$\end{document}). Mopourisetty et al.7 have reported an electrical study for 1 µm TF C-Si-SC with surface recombination losses at a Si/SiO2 interface with a Jsc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${J}_{sc}$$\end{document} of 11.9 mA cm−2. Yang et al.8 have introduced 2 µm TF C-Si-SC with partially embedded dielectric sphere with a photocurrent density (Jph\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
